==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mantelletta
<hw>Man`tel*let"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>mantelletta</ets>. See <er>Mantelet</er>.]</ety> <fld>(R. C.
Ch.)</fld> <def>A silk or woolen vestment without sleeves worn by
cardinals, bishops, abbots, and the prelates of the Roman court. It has
a low collar, is fastened in front, and reaches almost to the
knees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mantelpiece</ent>⟦br⟧
